# Foundry RFD3 isolated runtime note

Backend name: `foundry_rfd3`

Foundry RFD3 is the stack's all-atom/contact-aware backbone generation backend.
Foundry RF3 is reserved for folding/prediction confirmation.

Expected TYL runtime:

```text
Repo: ~/protein_design/repos/foundry
Env: ~/protein_design/envs/foundry-rfd3
Checkpoints: ~/protein_design/weights/foundry
Package: rc-foundry 0.2.0
Python: 3.12.13
Torch: 2.6.0+cu124
```

Install:

```bash
sbatch ~/protein_design/scripts/slurm_templates/install_foundry_micromamba.sbatch
```

Repair torch/CUDA if needed:

```bash
sbatch ~/protein_design/scripts/slurm_templates/repair_foundry_torch_cuda124.sbatch
```

Run via the unified launcher:

```bash
BACKBONE_BACKEND=foundry_rfd3 \
INPUT_PDB=/path/to/reference.pdb \
MOTIF_TSV=/path/to/motif_residues.tsv \
RUN_ROOT=/path/to/run \
NUM_DESIGNS=10 \
  sbatch ~/protein_design/scripts/slurm_templates/run_backbone_generation.sbatch
```
